CORE INFRASTRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Electron + React + TypeScript desktop app
- SQLite database (database.ts) with base tables:
  teams, players, games, stats, contracts, settings, champions,
  draft_prospects, depth_chart, career_stats_history, hall_of_fame,
  historical_records, news_events, pick_assets, team_trade_overrides,
  player_milestones, dead_cap_entries, coaching_staff, team_schemes,
  owner_goals, injury_history, team_chemistry, chemistry_events, scouts,
  team_finances, expansion_history
- Schema version: v20. Migration runner in runMigrations() upgrades existing
  saves on launch. Active migrations:
  v9:  team_id INTEGER on career_stats_history + idx_career_stats_team
  v10: Recalibrate all active-roster contract salaries to market-rate scale
  v11: Normalize all team salary totals to 95% of salary cap (~$265M)
  v12: owner_goals table; owner_patience setting initialized to 75
  v13: injury_history table; injury_prone INTEGER column on players
  v14: team_chemistry table (team_id, chemistry 0–100);
       chemistry_events table (team_id, season, week, delta, reason);
       all 32 teams seeded with chemistry = 50 on migration
  v15: archetype TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'normal' column on players
       (existing players all start as 'normal'; new players get weighted
       random archetype from generatePlayers / replenishFAPool)
  v16: scouts table (id, team_id, first_name, last_name, overall_rating,
       specialty, salary, years_on_staff); 2 scouts seeded per team + 40
       free-agent scouts generated on first launch via ScoutingService
  v17: games.play_log TEXT column — stores JSON-serialized play-by-play log
       generated by generatePlayLog() after each simulated game
  v18: team_finances table (team_id UNIQUE, market_size, stadium_capacity,
       season_revenue, owner_budget); seeded for all 32 teams with
       differentiated market data on migration
  v19: is_expansion INTEGER DEFAULT 0, stadium_name TEXT, relocated_from TEXT
       columns added to teams table; expansion_history table created
       (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, team_name TEXT, city TEXT, abbrev TEXT,
       season INTEGER); salary_cap setting seeded to 279000000 on migration
  v20: attendance_rate REAL DEFAULT 0.85 on team_finances;
       gm_personality TEXT DEFAULT 'balanced' on teams;
       is_rookie_deal INTEGER DEFAULT 0, fifth_year_option_eligible INTEGER
       DEFAULT 0, fifth_year_option_picked_up INTEGER DEFAULT 0 on contracts;
       holdout_status TEXT DEFAULT 'none', holdout_weeks INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
       trade_demand INTEGER DEFAULT 0 on players;
       GM personalities seeded randomly across all 32 teams;
       attendance_rates seeded per team
- Salary cap is dynamic: stored in settings under key 'salary_cap'. All
  contract logic reads it via getSalaryCap() helper (src/helpers/getSalaryCap.ts)
  which falls back to 279000000 if not set. Cap escalates via LeagueExpansionService.
- generateContracts() uses CONTRACT_MARKET_RATES table + TRAIT_PREMIUM
  multipliers. After generation every team scaled to 95% of salary cap.
- career_stats_history: player_id, season, team_id, games, completions,
  pass/rush/rec stats, defensive stats, def_tds.
- DB indexes:
  stats: game_id, player_id, team_id, (team_id,game_id), (season,is_playoff)
  games: season, (season,is_simulated), (season,week,is_playoff)
  career_stats_history: player_id, (player_id,season), team_id
  news_events: (season,week), (season,category)
  contracts: team_id, player_id
  depth_chart: (team_id,position_group)
  pick_assets: (owner_team_id,season)
  draft_prospects: season
  players: (team_id,roster_status), roster_status
  injury_history: player_id
  chemistry_events: (team_id,season)
- player_milestones: PRIMARY KEY (player_id, milestone_key)
- 32 fictional teams auto-seeded on first launch (AFC/NFC, 4 divisions each)
- Fictional player generator: 53 players per team + 176 free agents on fresh
  start; each player receives a weighted random archetype
- Multiple save files — save picker at launch, lazy DB init via Proxy
- Season advance prunes: news_events kept to last 3 seasons; raw stats kept to
  current + prior season
- Branded splash screen (src/index.html): renders before React, animated orange
  progress bar, fades via window.__hideSplash()

CODE ARCHITECTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Game simulation modularized into src/sim/:
  types.ts      — shared TeamRatings, GameResult, GamePlayerStat interfaces;
                  TeamData includes chemistry: number
  ratings.ts    — loadTeamData() loads players, coaches, scheme, chemistry;
                  computeTeamRatings() applies morale, coaching, scheme, and
                  chemistry modifiers
  stats.ts      — player stat generation per position
  scoring.ts    — weather, quarter scoring, overtime
  playbyplay.ts — generatePlayLog() builds play-by-play log from game stats;
                  PlayEntry: { quarter, teamName, description, type, homeScore,
                  awayScore }; type is one of td/fg/turnover/bigplay; phrase
                  banks for TD pass (4 variants), TD run (4 variants), FG (3),
                  turnover (3), big play (3); called after simulate-game and
                  simulate-week, stored in games.play_log / settingsRepo
  simulateGame.ts — thin orchestrator; accepts optional GamePlanOptions param
- Preload modularized into src/preload/ (11 domain files):
  core.ts, season.ts, roster.ts, contracts.ts, trades.ts, draft.ts,
  stats.ts, coaching.ts, injuries.ts, chemistry.ts, gameprep.ts
  core.ts exposes: setSetting(key, value), getSetting(key),
  applyDynastyTemplate(), getTeamFinances(teamId), getAllTeamFinances()
  stats.ts exposes: getGamePlayLog(gameId) — fetches play-by-play log for
  a completed game; fetched in parallel with box score via Promise.all;
  importCareerStats() — triggers import-career-stats IPC (file dialog → CSV
  parsed → rows matched by first_name+last_name → upserted into career_stats_history)
  season.ts exposes: getLeagueOfficeData(), castExpansionVote(vote),
  getRelocationCities(), requestUserRelocation(cityObj), getRecentLeagueEvents(),
  getAllGmPersonalities(), initPlayoffs(season), getPlayoffState(season),
  simulatePlayoffGame(gameId)
  contracts.ts exposes: advanceOffseasonPhase() — advances offseason phase via
  advance-offseason-phase IPC; used by Home.tsx handleAdvancePhase handler
  preload.ts merges all via spread into a single contextBridge exposure.
- IPC handlers split by domain in src/handlers/:
  simHandlers, seasonHandlers, settingsHandlers, statsHandlers,
  contractHandlers, tradeHandlers, draftHandlers, importHandlers,
  newsHandlers, saveHandlers, coachingHandlers, schemeHandlers,
  injuryHandlers, chemistryHandlers
- Services layer in src/services/:
  SeasonService, SimulationService, StatsService, TradeService,
  ContractService, CoachingService, ProgressionService, OwnerGoalsService,
  InjuryService, ChemistryService, ScoutingService, LeagueExpansionService,
  LeagueEventsService
  LeagueEventsService: 10 predefined narrative events (attendance_surge,
  salary_cap_controversy, star_injury_scare, weather_disaster, stadium_upgrade,
  blockbuster_trade_rumor, coaching_carousel, rule_change, expansion_fever,
  record_contract); checkLeagueEvents() fires one per season at 45% chance;
  getRecentLeagueEvents(n) retrieves last n events from news_events
  LeagueExpansionService: checkCapEscalation (10% chance/season, cap grows
  2–5%, stored in settings salary_cap), checkExpansionVote (city pool,
  user vote threshold 60%+, inserts expansion_history row), checkCpuRelocation
  (patience-driven CPU team city moves, logs news event)
- Repositories layer in src/repositories/ — typed DB access per domain;
  includes ScoutRepository (getByTeam, getAvailable, getById, assignToTeam,
  release, getWeeklyPoints)
- Helpers in src/helpers/:
  getSalaryCap.ts — reads 'salary_cap' from settings table; fallback 279000000.
  Used everywhere ContractService and LeagueExpansionService need the current cap.
  logNewsEvent.ts — logs typed news event objects (eventType, category, headline,
  detail, teamId, playerId, season, week) to news_events table.
- Shared UI components in src/components/:
  ArchetypeBadge.tsx — reusable archetype chip; import anywhere;
  renders nothing when archetype === 'normal'

