    season data. Inserts teams from CSV; regenerates players + contracts via
    generatePlayers() + generateContracts(). Validates conference/division/abbr.
    Required: city, name, abbreviation, conference, division.
    IPC: import-custom-teams
  STEP 2 — CUSTOM PLAYERS / ROSTER: replaces all players + contracts. Teams unchanged.
    If annual_salary + years_remaining columns present, uses CSV values directly;
    otherwise auto-generates contracts from OVR ratings. Validates team_abbreviation.
    Required: first_name, last_name, position.
    IPC: import-custom-players
  STEP 3 — CAREER STATS: seeds per-season career stat lines for imported players.
    Matches rows to player_id by first_name + last_name. Skips unmatched rows (count
    reported). Upserts via ON CONFLICT(player_id, season) DO UPDATE SET. Supports all
    career_stats_history columns including defensive stats and team_abbreviation.
    Required: first_name, last_name, season.
    IPC: import-career-stats (importHandlers.ts)
  STEP 4 — ALL-TIME RECORDS: replaces all-time leaderboard benchmarks shown in Records
    tab. Clears record_type='alltime' rows then bulk inserts. Same schema as season records.
    Required: category, rank, player_name.
    IPC: import-historical-records('alltime')
  STEP 5 — SEASON RECORDS: replaces single-season record benchmarks in Records tab.
    Clears record_type='season' rows then bulk inserts. Requires season column.
    Required: category, rank, player_name, season.
    IPC: import-historical-records('season')
- formatResult() handles all three result shapes: {imported, skipped} for career stats,
  {imported, contractsGenerated} for players, {imported} for others
- NFL real-world data files generated from Madden 2025 ratings + nflverse stats +
  OTC contract data (kept off-repo for licensing); 5 files: nfl_teams.csv,
  nfl_players.csv, nfl_career_stats.csv, nfl_alltime_records.csv, nfl_season_records.csv

GAME SIMULATION ENGINE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Stats-first scoring: TDs/FGs from team ratings; player stats match scoreboard
- Realistic 18-game schedule: 6 divisional, 8 intra-conf, 4 inter-conf per team
- Team rating pipeline (computeTeamRatings):
  1. Position-weighted base ratings
  2. Morale modifier: effOVR = rating x (1 + (morale - 75) x 0.001)
  3. Coaching modifier: OC/DC +0.15x, HC +0.05x (vs. 70 baseline)
  4. Scheme modifier: roster fit bonus/penalty
  5. Chemistry modifier: -4 to +3 based on team_chemistry value
- GamePlanOptions: optional offense/defense mode passed to simulateGame();
  read from settings key gameplan_{season}_{week}; applied as rating multipliers:
  Offense modes: balanced (default), spread (+pass -run), power_run (+run -pass),
  west_coast (+short pass efficiency), play_action (+play action bonus)
  Defense modes: base (default), blitz (+pass rush -coverage), zone_coverage
  (+coverage -rush D), press (+man coverage), prevent (+deep coverage -rush)
- CPU game plan: derived from team scheme setting (West Coast/Spread →
  pass_attack, Air Raid → bombs_away, Pro Style → balanced, Power Run →
  run_heavy; 4-3 → base, 3-4 → zone, Nickel → press_man, Dime → zone, 46 →
  blitz); applied via GamePlanOptions for CPU teams
- Play-by-Play log: generatePlayLog() called after every game; PlayEntry fields:
  quarter (1–4), teamName, description (template phrase), type (td/fg/turnover/
  bigplay), homeScore, awayScore; stored in games.play_log TEXT column;
  retrieved via get-game-play-log IPC; non-critical (failure silently skipped);
  rendered in box score modal on Home tab, grouped by quarter
- Game script: trailing teams pass more; leading teams run more
- Overtime: TD wins outright; FG gives opponent a chance; no ties
- Weather: clear / rain / snow / wind with pass, rush, score multipliers
- Home field advantage: +0.5 scoring drives; away QB accuracy penalty
- Depth chart integration: healthy players cascade to backups
- Background simulation: simulateGame runs in a worker thread (simWorker)

SEASON ADVANCE (advanceSeason in SeasonService.ts)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 1. Age all non-retired players
 2. Progression / regression by dev trait + age bracket
 3. Breakout bonuses for standout season performers (age <= 28)
 4. Practice squad development (age <= 23, up to +3 OVR)
 5. Dev trait evolution
 6. Retirement (age/OVR thresholds, chance-based)
 7. Morale update (win%, contract year, playing time)
 8. Open free agency (CPU GM cuts + resign + contract expiry)
 9. Contract demand news events (elite players, final year)
10. Injury + waiver cleanup
11. Archive season stats to career_stats_history (with team_id)
12. Prune raw stats (DELETE WHERE season < current - 1)
13. Prune news events (keeps 3 seasons)
14. HOF inductions for newly retired players
15. Season award news events (MVP, DPOY)
16. Evaluate owner goals + update patience
17. Advance season counter
18. Replenish FA pool
19. Check cap escalation (LeagueExpansionService.checkCapEscalation) —
    10% chance per offseason; cap grows 2–5%; new value stored in settings
    under key 'salary_cap'; all future contract logic reads via getSalaryCap()
20. Check expansion vote (LeagueExpansionService.checkExpansionVote) —
    draws a random city from pool; reads user vote from 'user_expansion_vote'
    setting; 60%+ combined threshold triggers expansion; inserts row into
    expansion_history and seeds a new teams record (is_expansion = 1);
    clears 'user_expansion_vote' setting after resolution
21. Check CPU relocation (LeagueExpansionService.checkCpuRelocation) —
    CPU teams with critically low patience may relocate to an available city;
    updates team city/name/abbrev in DB; sets relocated_from to original city;
    logs a 'League' category news event via logNewsEvent()
22. Recalculate dynamic revenue (recalculateTeamFinances) — updates
    season_revenue in team_finances based on market_size × win_pct modifier
    × attendance_rate; large market teams benefit more from winning
23. Check holdouts and trade demands (checkHoldoutsAndDemands in
    ContractService) — players with low morale + final year contracts may
    enter holdout or demand a trade; sets holdout_status / trade_demand flags
24. Check random league events (checkLeagueEvents in LeagueEventsService) —
    45% chance one of 10 predefined events fires each season; logged to
    news_events; effects may modify attendance_rate, revenue, or draft class

IN-SEASON PLAYER PROGRESSION (ProgressionService.ts)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Runs after every simulated game
- gradePerformance(): 0–100 grade by position from game stats
- calcDelta(): OVR delta from grade + age modifier + dev trait bonus +
  archetype bonus (hard_worker +20% / coachable +12% extra gain chance) +
  OVR ceiling dampening + OVR floor protection
- Breakout news events on 2+ OVR gain or young standout

CPU GM INTELLIGENCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Team classification: Contender / Buyer / Neutral / Seller / Rebuilding
- gm_personality column on teams (schema v20): aggressive, conservative,
  balanced, rebuilder, win_now — seeded randomly at v20 migration
- Personality modifiers applied in ContractService CPU FA bidding and resign:
  aggressive: bids 10–15% above market; win_now: 8% premium on vets;
  rebuilder: -10% on vets, +20% value on youth; conservative: -5% all;
  balanced: no modifier
- Cap cleanup, CPU resign (78%–110% of market), FA bidding engine
- CPU incoming trades: max 2/week; 18% weekly chance; weeks 1–10 only

ROOKIE CONTRACT SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Slotted salary scale applied at draft time (draftHandlers.ts):
  Round 1 Picks 1–5: $7.5M–$5.0M; Picks 6–10: $4.5M–$3.2M;
  Picks 11–32: $2.8M–$1.8M; Round 2: $1.2M–$0.9M; Rounds 3–7: $0.85M
- Contracts marked is_rookie_deal = 1; all Round 1 picks get
  fifth_year_option_eligible = 1
- 5th-year option: pick up or decline via IPC pick-up-fifth-year-option /
  decline-fifth-year-option; displayed in OffseasonTab and SalariesTab
  with badge indicators

HOLDOUT & TRADE DEMAND SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- checkHoldoutsAndDemands() runs at season advance (step 23)
- Trigger conditions: morale < 50 AND final contract year AND OVR >= 75
  → 30% chance of holdout; OVR >= 82 and morale < 40 → 20% trade demand
- Resolution options (IPC resolve-holdout): pay (grant raise via extend),
  wait (holdout continues, -5 morale), trade_request (mark for trade)
- holdout_weeks incremented each season advance while unresolved
- OffseasonTab displays holdout panel with player cards and action buttons

MILESTONE SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Runs after every week and game sim
- 9 career categories, 26 thresholds, 5 single-season thresholds
- Fires exactly once per player per threshold

WAIVER WIRE SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- In-season releases → waivers; offseason → free_agent
- processWaivers() at end of each week; worst-record-first CPU claims

FA POOL REPLENISHMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- MIN_FA_PER_POSITION: QB:10, RB:22, WR:28, TE:14, OL:28, DL:24, LB:24, CB:24,
  S:18, K:6 (doubled from original to create a meaningful FA market each offseason)
- New FAs get weighted random archetype via genArchetype()

